description:
"Sometimes it's not what the leaders say publicly that shapes the outcome. A memo by an assistant can mean the difference between war and peace."
—Kai

name: Deno's Fish Hook
description:
"The trick is a little rabbit fur around the top, and tie it down with a little luck all around."
—Deno

name: Stone Of Rinn
description:
"Ghosts hate tresspassers, and the branded hate everything. Take some stones from one ruin, put it by some branded, and you'll have a battle in no time."
—Erria

name: Iron Legion Badge of Bravery
description:
"The Iron Legion thanks you. Maybe now we can get back to fixing up this blasted fort."
—Engineer Burlage Firestoker

name: Ogre Pet Tags
description:
"They say the Ogres infuse these with some kind of magic. Thus the bond with their pets. We just collect them because it's fun."
—Avarr Sneakpaw

name: Tiny Crystal Shard
description:
"Those silly monkies will worship anything. Enjoy this tiny pockey sized "Star God"
—Olenn

name: Flashing Mine Blinker
description:
"Skritt rip these out of the mines all the time. Looks like this one survived the explosion. The skritt didn't."
—Faithspotter

name: Scriptures of Dwayna
description:
"The writing in these are ancient and beautiful. Makes you wonder what else was lost when Ascalon fell."
—Jinell

name: Pressed Friendship Flower
description:
"Thank you friend of Degun Shun."
—Shelp

name: Sentinel's Scout Badge
description:
"Thank you for your help. Your work helps us get rid of those trouble making inquest."
—Sentinel Liharn

name: Harpy Love Memento
description:
"As much as you try to understand it. Alchemically speaking, love is still a mystery, even to my genius intellect."
—Wode

name: Night Vision Enhancers
description:
"Darkness, like anything else, is best when its enhanced."
—Fina Duskmaker

name: Bomb Fuse
description:
"Careful what sparks you create."
—Jahr Duskrend

name: Scout Commendation Letter
description:
"On behalf of the Sentinels, thank you."
—Fahrtak Shatterfiend

name: Sweptweave Schematic
description:
"Everything starts with a plan, but nothing ever goes according to it."
—Torruh Sweptweave

name: Signed Pact Agreement
description:
"We printed extra copies in case any disagreements came up in the field. This way we are all on the same page."
—Agent Crandle

name: Golem Cannon Blueprint
description:
"In case I don't make it, this will prove I was a genius!"
—Explorer Trebb

name: Trebuchet Counterweight
description:
"The greater the strike, the greater the counterblow."
—Crusader Vilborg

name: Ancient Emerald Orrian Spoon
description:
"These are pretty. So pretty."
—Recruit Tochacatl

name: Goldenlight Hallow Lab Test Results
description:
"Normally only krewe members get to see these, but seeing how you helped generate the more interesting data points you can have them."
—Krewe Leader Seesa

name: Mechanical Golem Eye
description:
"So many shiny things when they blow up on landing."
—Explorer Grretergrret

name: Kamekeck War Paint
description:
"Most powerful paint. Powerful magic for powerful battle."
—Marksman Kamekeck

name: Order Of Whispers Tactical Operations Manual
description:

—Agent Siobhan

name: Letter Home
description:

—Diah

name: Drake Scale
description:
"Did you see the size of that thing?"
—Travis

name: Harpy Feather
description:
"So, here's the thing: you can have lots of harpies, or we can finish this dam, but I don't think you can have both."
—Flannum

name: Measuring Spoon
description:
"Make sure to use heaping spoonfuls."
—Eda

name: Moa Collar
description:
"Our moas prefer the spiked collars."
—Cassie

name: Seraph Emblem
description:
"You paid for this in centaur blood."
—Diedra

name: Shiny Skritt Trinket
description:
"Skritt will steal anything not nailed down, and even then it better be nailed to something big."
—Laborer Cardy

name: Rare Ascalonian Coin
description: <c=@flavor>The emblem for King Adelbern is barely recognizable, and the writing has been completely worn off.</c>

name: Claypool Militia Badge
description: <c=@flavor>"Trained Member of the Claypool Militia"</c>

name: Centaur Arrowhead
description: <c=@flavor>"It's chipped and stained with old blood."</c>

name: Boar Tusk
description:
"If you think this one is big, you should see the one above the fireplace."
—Hunter Block

name: Monk's Beer Stein
description:
"These steins are crafted extra sturdy. They won't break over a bandit's head, and the can block a centaur arrow without leaking any ale."
—Brother Vince

name: Fish Hook
description:
"This is my own special hook design that I carve out of dried driftwood."
—Fisherman Will

name: Chewed Dog Whistle
description:
"Whatever dog got hold of this whistle has really big teeth."
—Paden

name: Rusty Iron Key
description: <c=@flavor>"There's more rust than iron left here."</c>

name: Ettin Nose Ring
description:
"Ettin ring make you strong!"
—Krug

name: Petrified Ectoplasm
description:
"Why did they come here? What were these used for? If only I could find the answers."
—Historian Garrod

name: Seraph Dog Tags
description: <c=@flavor>"The inscription worn and illegible."</c>
